column5: Title
column7: Description

column5: স্থানাঙ্ক জ্যামিতি(Coordinate Geometry) - Bengali Maths
column7: This video explains 'Co-ordinate Geometry' and its basic applications. Important theorems related to co-ordinate geometry are then explained including Pythagoras' theorem.

column5: সরলরেখাংশের অন্তর্বিভক্তও বহির্বিভক্ত (Division of Straight Line Segments) - Bengali Maths
column7: This video illustrates the idea behind similar triangles and how to apply that basic geometry to find out formulas for dividing a straight line internally and externally.

column5: এিভুজাকৃতি ক্ষেএেরক্ষেএফল (Area of a triangular region) - Bengali Maths
column7: This video explains how to calculate area of a triangle using co-ordinate geometry. The formula is derived first and it is then followed by illustrative examples.

column5: বহুপদী সংখ্যামালা(Polynomials) - Bengali Maths
column7: This video is based on the chapter "Polynomials" of the West Bengal state board.

column5: গুন্নতর প্রগতি (Geometric Progression) - Bengali Maths
column7: Geometric progression and the related terms, like common ratio etc. are explained in this video. The formulae for the sum of a geometric progress for both finite and infinite series are derived and explained.

column5: গুন্নতর প্রগতি (প্রশ্ন ও উত্তর) | Geometric Progression (Questions and answers) | Bengali Maths
column7: This video consists of solved examples for the topic geometric progressions, whose theory was explained in an earlier video.

column5: ভুপাশেত্র এবং ঘনফল ভাগ1 (Surface Area and Volume Part 1) - Bengali Maths
column7: This video introduces Surface Area and Volume for common solids. In this particular video, cube and cuboid are covered.

column5: ভুপাশেত্র এবং ঘনফল ভাগ2 (Surface Area and Volume Part 2) - Bengali Maths
column7: This video covers cylinder and cone. The expressions for surface area and volume are explained.

column5: বৃত্ত - অংশ 1/2 (Circle - Part 1/2) - Bengali Maths
column7: In this video, various terminologies related to a circle like chord, major arc, minor arc, diameter, etc. are explained.

column5: বৃত্ত - অংশ 2/2 (Circle - Part 2/2) - Bengali Maths
column7: In this video, various theorems related to circles are discussed, like the bisector of a chord being perpendicular to it, equality of angles subtended by a chord, etc.

column5: দ্বিঘাত সমীকরণ - ভাগ 1/3 (Quadratic Equations - Part 1/3) - Bengali Maths
column7: In this video, characteristics of quadratic equations are discussed. Factorization and formula method for finding the roots are explained. The concept of discriminant is discussed and the subsequently nature of roots is explained.

column5: দ্বিঘাত সমীকরণ - ভাগ 2/3 (Quadratic Equations - Part 2/3) - Bengali Maths
column7: This video covers various solved examples based on the formula method and factorization method taught in the last class.

column5: দ্বিঘাত সমীকরণ - ভাগ 3/3 (Quadratic Equations - Part 3/3)
column7: This video covers the nature of the roots of a quadratic equation based on the discriminant. It also shows the parabolic plot of a quadratic equations.

column5: ত্রিকোণমিতি ভাগ ১(Trigonometry Part 1)
column7: In this video, a motivation for trigonometry is built, it's importance is explained. Also, the trigonometric ratios like sin, cos, tan etc. are explained.

column5: ত্রিকোণমিতি ভাগ ২(Trigonometry Part 2)
column7: In this video, you will learn relations between the trigonometric ratios sin, cos, tan etc. You will also learn trigonometric identities with their proof, and how to remember them too.

column5: ত্রিকোণমিতি ভাগ ৩(Trigonometry Part 3)
column7: Learn how to represent one trigonometric ratio in terms of another ratio, and also practice different types of problems on trigonometry.

column5: ত্রিকোণমিতি ভাগ ৪(Trigonometry Part 4)
column7: Learn what the values of sin, cos, tan, cosec, sec and cot are for the angles 0°, 30°, 45°, 60° and 90°. Learn to solve a few problems and proofs too involving these concepts.

column5: ত্রিকোণমিতি ভাগ ৫(Trigonometry Part 5)
column7: Learn how to find out the value of a trigonometric equation, and with a few tricks to make it easier.

column5: ত্রিকোণমিতি ভাগ ৬(Trigonometry Part 6)
column7: In this video, approach to various trigonometric problems is explained using the concepts learnt in the previous five parts.

column5: সমান্তর প্রগতি (Arithmetic Progression)
column7: Learn what is a Series, Arithmetic Progression, the Nth term and Sum of an Arithmetic Progression along-with some examples to elaborate these concepts.

column5: বাস্তব সংখ্যা ভাগ ১ (Real Numbers)
column7: Learn about Natural numbers, Whole numbers, Integers and Rational numbers.

column5: 1000 Subscribers | The OLI Journey | A Tribute to the Viewers
column7: Yipee!! We have reached 1000 subscribers!! Celebration is in the air. In this special video hosted by OLI's founder, Yash Sanghvi, we take a look at the amazing journey of this YouTube channel. We hope you'll like it. This video is also a token of gratitude from our side to you, our wonderful audience, without whom, nothing would have been possible. Please keep supporting in the same way in the future as well.

column5: OLI First Year Lookback
column7: This video takes you through all the achievements of OLI in the past one year and also gives an overview of our plan for the next year.

column5: December Bonanza 2015
column7: Learn a lot this december with OLI. With minimum one video per day and videos in two more regional languages, namely Malayalam and Telugu and a new playlist containing videos demonstrating common scientific experiments, there is a lot for you this December. Happy Learning!!

column5: ત્રિકોણ (Triangle) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video explains 'Triangles' and begins with important definitions related to triangles. Important theorems related to triangles are then explained including congruence theorems. The video ends with a discussion of the various inequalities in a triangle.

column5: વાસ્તવિક સંખ્યા (Real Numbers) - Gujarati Maths
column7: Real numbers is introduced and the difference between real, rational, irrational numbers etc. is explained. Representing real numbers on the number line is explained. Representation of rational numbers in decimal format is explained and operations on real numbers are covered with illustrative examples.

column5: ભૂમિતિનું માળખું(Structure of Geometry) - Gujarati Maths
column7: The important concepts related to geometry, like axioms, postulates, theorems etc. are discussed. Important geometrical phrases, like "at least", "at most" etc. are discussed and different types of statements, like conditional, biconditional etc. are introduced.

column5: શક્યતા (Probability) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video introduces Probability through some motivational examples before taking a more formal approach for the same. Concepts of Sample space, Event, Complement of an Event etc. are introduced through motivational examples. The video concludes with a short quiz.

column5: ત્રિકોણમિતિ(Trigonometry) - Gujarati Maths
column7: The video begins with a few motivating examples that illustrate the applications of Trigonometry. Trigonometric ratios are later explained and the important equalities concerning them are discussed. The video then moves on to explain the concept of complementary angles and the relations between the trigonometric ratios of complementary angles. Some other important equations concerning trigonometric equations are then discussed and the video ends with an example which illustrates the use of equations to solve trigonometric problems.

column5: બહુપદી (Polynomials) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video begins with a examples of applications of polynomials and explains why learning polynomials is important. The graphical representation of polynomials is later explained. The relationship between the co-efficients and roots of the polynomials is then taken up. Finally, the video explains the methods of division of polynomials, which includes synthetic division.

column5: સમાંતર શ્રેણી (Arithmetic Progression) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video begins by explaining the importance of sequences in real life and builds the motivation for the chapter. Important terminologies related to Arithmetic Progression are then explained. Illustrative examples are distributed throughout the video to help the students understand the concepts better.

column5: ગણક્રિયાઓ (Set Operations): ભાગ 1/2 (Part 1/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video begins with the revision of the content that that students are expected to have covered till Class 8. Union and Intersection and their properties are later studied in great detail with illustrative examples.

column5: ગણક્રિયાઓ (Set Operations): ભાગ 2/2 (Part 2/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video states and proves distributive and De Morgan's laws using Venn Diagrams. A question is solved at the end to demonstrate the use of these laws.

column5: આંકડાશાસ્ત્ર (Statistics): ભાગ 1/2 (Part 1/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video focusses on the class 9 syllabus. The video begins with an introduction of statistics and explains its significance. The common statistical terms such as data, range frequency etc. are explained. Methods of representing data, such as bar diagrams, histograms and frequency polygons are explained. Mean, median and mode are later discussed. Illustrative examples are distributed throughout the text.

column5: આંકડાશાસ્ત્ર (Statistics): ભાગ 2/2 (Part 2/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video focusses on the class 10 syllabus. Mean, median and mode are discussed and the formulae for calculating them for grouped data are given. The relation among these three measures of central tendency is given at the end of the video.

column5: અંતર અને ઉંચાઈ(Distance and Height) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video begins with an explanation of the basic concepts, i.e., horizontal ray, ray of vision, angle of elevation and angle of depression. After the concepts are explained, three illustrative examples are given to further demonstrate the utility of these concepts with trigonometry.

column5: પૃષ્ઠફળ અને ઘનફળ(Surface Area and Volume): ભાગ 1/2 (Part 1/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video focusses on the class 9 syllabus. It begins with examples of applications of the surface area (both total and curved surface area, wherever applicable) and volume formulae in real life. After that, the formulae for cuboid, cube, cylinder, cone and sphere are stated with derivation wherever possible. In most cases, the complex shape is broken down to simpler shapes and the corresponding formulae are then derived. This is followed by a few solved examples.

column5: પૃષ્ઠફળ અને ઘનફળ(Surface Area and Volume): ભાગ 2/2 (Part 2/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video focusses on class 10 syllabus. It begins with a motivation for the topic. Later, the methods of finding surface area and volume of an assembly of different shapes is explained with illustrative examples. Frustum of a cone is then explained with some illustrative examples.

column5: રચનાઓ(Constructions): ભાગ1/2 (Part 1/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7:
This video is based on the Class 9 syllabus. The methods of construction of the following are discussed:
1. Bisector of an angle
2. Perpendicular bisector of a straight line segment
3. An angle of measure 60 degrees
4. A triangle whose base, one base angle and the sum of measures of other two sides is given
5. A triangle whose base, one base angle and the difference between the measures of other two sides is given
6. A triangle when both the base angles and the perimeter is given

All the steps are clearly explained and the the mathematical principles behind each construction are properly explained.

column5: રચનાઓ(Constructions): ભાગ2/2 (Part 2/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7:
Published on Dec 19, 2015
This video focusses on the class 10 syllabus. The following is explained:
1. Dividing a line segment in a given ratio
2. Constructing a triangle similar to a given triangle and in a given ratio to the given triangle
3. Constructing the tangent to a circle from points on and outside the circle.

All steps are clearly explained and animations are used for better understanding.

column5: યામ ભૂમિતિ (Co-ordinate Geometry) - Gujarati Maths
column7: This video gives an introduction to co-ordinate geometry. The Cartesian Coordinate system is defined and other important definitions (axis, origin, quadrants etc.) are given. The method of finding the co-ordinates of a point in the cartesian plane is explained. Also, the method of plotting a point with given coordinates is explained with illustrative examples.

column5: દ્વિચલ સુરેખ સમીકરણ (Linear Equation in Two Variables) - Gujarati Maths
column7: In this video, you learn learn what are linear equations and how they are useful to us in our daily lives. Also, you will learn about the general form of a linear equation in two variables, as well as how to find its solution.

column5: સંખ્યા પદ્ધતિ ભાગ 1 (Number System Part 1) - Gujarati Maths
column7: Learn about Natural numbers, Whole numbers, Integers, Rational numbers as well as Irrational numbers, and how to differentiate between them.

column5: સંખ્યા પદ્ધતિ ભાગ 2 (Number System Part 2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: In this video, you will be introduced to the concept of number lines and real numbers, as well as, how the real numbers are placed on the number line.

column5: સંખ્યા પદ્ધતિ ભાગ 3 (Number System Part 3) - Gujarati Maths
column7: In this video you will learn what are decimal numbers, and what do we mean by terminating and non-terminating decimal numbers. Also, we will learn how to find the decimal expansion of rational and irrational numbers.

column5: દ્વિચલ સુરેખ સમીકરણ (Linear Equation in Two Variables): ભાગ 2/2 (Part 2/2) - Gujarati Maths
column7: In this video, you will learn about the graphs of linear equation in two variables. You will also see some solved examples which will help you study the graphs.

column5: ધાતુઓ (ભાગ ૧) - Metals (Part 1)
column7: Learn about the various processes involved in the extraction and purification of metals using metallurgical processes.

column5: ધાતુઓ (ભાગ ૨) - Metals (Part 2)
column7: Learn how to extract aluminium from Bauxite, how a blast furnace extracts iron, the Metals Activity Series, and also the physical and chemical properties of metals.

column5: ધાતુઓ (ભાગ ૩) - Metals (Part 3)
column7: Learn about Corrosion, methods to prevent corrosion, Alloys, Purity of gold and some chemical reactions of metals.

column5: भिम ऍप कैसे उपयोग करे? (How to use BHIM App?) Tutorial - Cashless India - Hindi
column7: This video gives a step-by-step procedure for downloading, installing and using the BHIM app launched by the Prime Minister for cashless transactions, yesterday. The major features of the app are explained.

column5: डेबिट कार्ड एवम् क्रेडिट कार्ड(Debit and Credit Cards) - Cashless India - Hindi
column7: This video introduces the viewers to Debit and Credit cards, their key features and their key differences.

column5: USSD, UPI and Mobile Wallets (PayTM) Tutorial - Cashless India - Hindi
column7: In this video, mobile phone transactions are discussed for both smartphone and non-smartphone users. USSD for non-smartphone users and UPI and e-wallets for smartphone users are covered in detail. Sample transactions are shown for each method, covering most aspects of each transaction. Methods of downloading, installing and registering oneself in the relevant apps are also shown with the sample transactions. The requirements for using each method are listed out.

column5: Aadhaar Enabled Payment System (AEPS) Tutorial - Cashless India - Hindi
column7: In this video, learn how to make transactions using your Aadhaar card and a micro-ATM machine. Please note that there are fees associated with Aadhaar based transactions, which can go upto maximum of 15 rupees per transaction. Check the fee amount before the transaction.

column5: इन्टरनेट बैंकिंग (Internet Banking) Tutorial - Cashless India - Hindi
column7: In this video, various aspects of net banking, like ease, security, features etc. are discussed. An example of online shopping with net banking is given for better understanding. The meaning of common banking terms like RTGS, NEFT etc. is given. Some tips are given at the end to enhance security of the transactions.

column5: OLI का परिचय(Introduction to OLI)
column7: This video introduces Open Learning Initiative (OLI), and explains our aims and objectives. This video answers all the common questions related to OLI.

column5: दिसम्बर बोनान्जा २०१६ | December Bonanza 2016
column7: December Bonanza is back with more videos :D

column5: प्रकाश का परावर्तन(Reflection of Light) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the reflection of light and also the image formation by curved mirrors. Ray tracing is explained through examples and important terms related to curved mirrors are introduced.
column11: in next, following numbers mean different things

column5: प्रकाश का अपवर्तन(Refraction of Light) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the next major in optics after Reflection, namely, Refraction. A physical feel for the topic is given through real life examples and this is followed by the popular experiment of refraction through a glass slab. Snell's law is later introduced and refractive index is explained. The video ends with a problem that will test your concepts.
column14: even if there are 5 parts, first part is 0, part 2,3,4 is 1 and part 5 is 2

column5: लेंस (Lenses) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video introduces the reader to convex and concave lenses and explains the formation of image using these lenses. The video begins with examples of applications of lenses and explains why they form an important part of optics. Enlargement of image formed by a magnifying glass is explained. The sign convention to be followed when dealing with lenses is explained in detail. The lens formula is discussed and an illustrative problem is solved at the end which covers most of the concepts discussed in the video.
column14: 2 part video means first video is 0, second video is 2

column5: अम्ल, क्षारक एवं लवण(Acids, Bases and Salts) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान(Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with a general differentiation between acids, bases and salts. It then introduces various indicators and how to use them. After that, the reaction of acids and bases with metals and their carbonates and hydrogen carbonates are discussed. Neutralization is then explained, followed by reactions of acids and bases with metal oxides. After this, the similarities between acids and bases are studied. Their behaviour in water is also studied. Later on, the concepts of strength of acids and bases and pH scale are introduced. The video ends with a discussion on some commonly used compounds like bleaching powder, washing soda, baking soda etc.

column5: धातु एवं अधातु (Metals and Non-metals) - कक्षा10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: The video begins with a comparison of the physical properties of metals and non-metals. After that, the reactions of a metal with air, water and acids are explained. Later on, the reactions of a metal with the salts of another metal are explained and metals are arranged in order of their activity. Formation of compounds of metals and non-metals is explained later with properties of these ionic compounds explained. A large section of the video then focusses on the extraction and purification of metals. The video ends with a discussion on rusting.

column5: ऊर्जा के स्रोत (Sources of Energy) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान(Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: The video begins by explaining the properties of a good source of energy. Later on fossil fuels, thermal power plants, hydro power plants, energy from biomass, wind energy, solar energy, tidal energy and nuclear energy are discussed in detail.

column5: कार्बन और उसके यौगिक(Carbon and its Compounds) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: The video begins with an explanation of the nature of bonds formed by carbon. Special properties of carbon which make it so unique are then discussed. The discussion then moves to saturated and unsaturated hydrocarbons. Chain and ring structures, both with branches, are then discussed. Various functional groups are then introduced and homologous series is explained. Nomenclature of carbon compounds is then explained. Afterwards, chemical properties of carbon compounds are explained. After that, certain special compounds, namely, ethanol, ethanoic acid, and soaps and detergents are discussed.

column5: विद्युत (Electricity) - भाग १(Part 1) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान(Class X Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with an introduction to electric charge. Then the concepts of current and voltage are explained. Important electrical symbols are then discussed. Ohm's law is introduced and explained in detail and the concept of a resistor is simultaneously introduced.

column5: विद्युत (Electricity) - भाग २(Part 2) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान(Class X Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with an explanation of the various factors affecting resistance of a resistor, namely, resistivity, length, and area of cross section. The video then focuses on the series and parallel combination of resistances and the concept of equivalent resistance is introduced. A very good analogy is used to make the student understand the concepts. Illustrative examples are given at the end to further enhance the understanding of the topic. Though this video is quite long compared to the other videos on the channel, it is nevertheless very interesting and keeps the viewer engaged.

column5: विद्युत (Electricity) - भाग ३(Part 3) - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान(Class X Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with a short revision of the series and parallel combination of resistances taught in Part 2, with a slightly greater insight in these combinations. Later, the heating effects of electric current are discussed. Formulae for Power and Energy are derived and explained and students are given a feel for the formulae. An example is solved at the end for better understanding.

column5: नियंत्रण एवं समन्वय(Control & Coordination) - भाग १ - कक्षा 10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: In this video, parts of our nervous system like the brain, the spinal cord, etc. are explained. What happens during reflex action, transmission of signals inside the body etc. are explained with examples.

column5: मानव नेत्र भाग - १ (Human Eye Part - 1) कक्षा 10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: In this video, you will learn about the Human Eye and how the different parts in the eye help us see an image. You will also learn about vision disorders and how to cure them along with example numericals.

column5: मानव नेत्र भाग - २ (Human Eye Part - 2) कक्षा 10 विज्ञान (Class 10 Science) - Hindi
column7: In this video, you will learn about the dispersion of light and its scattering. You will also learn the reason for rainbow formation and blue colour of the sky.

column5: दो चर वाले रैखिक समीकरण(Linear Equations in Two Variables) : भाग1/2 (Part 1/2) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the basic concepts related to linear equations in two variables. The topics covered include definition, solution of linear equations in two variables and graphical representation. The video ends with a solved example that further strengthens the concepts of the students.

column5: दो चर वाले रैखिक समीकरण(Linear Equations in Two Variables) : भाग2/2 (Part 2/2) - Hindi
column7: This video teaches how to solve a pair of linear equations in two variables. Both algebraic and graphical methods are shown.

column5: निर्देशांक ज्यामिति (Co-ordinate Geometry): भाग 1/2 (Part 1/2) - Hindi
column7: This video focusses more on the class IX syllabus of co-ordinate geometry. It begins with a brief motivation behind co-ordinate geometry. Rene-Descartes Idea is explained next and the axes and quadrants are introduced. In the end, plotting of a point using the co-ordinate axes is explained.

column5: निर्देशांक ज्यामिति (Co-ordinate Geometry): भाग 2/2 (Part 2/2) - Hindi
column7: This video focusses more on the class X syllabus of co-ordinate geometry. It starts with the distance formula which is one of the most basic and useful formulas of co-ordinate geometry. Later on, section formula and mid-point formula are introduced and explained in detail. At the end, finding the area of a triangle using co-ordinate geometry is indicated.

column5: त्रिभुज भाग १/३ - सर्वांगसमता (Triangle Part 1/3 - Congruence) - Hindi
column7: This video takes up the topic of congruence of triangles and begins with its definition. Various tests for congruence are later explained. Many illustrative examples and optional questions for the viewer to answer are distributed throughout the video.

column5: त्रिभुज भाग २/३ - असमिकाएँऔर समरूपता (Triangle Part 2/3 - Inequalities and Similarity) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the three main triangle inequalities with illustrative examples. Later on, similarity of triangles and the tests for similarity are explained and some sample problems are solved for better understanding of the students.

column5: त्रिभुज भाग ३/३- समरूपताजारी (Triangle Part 3/3 - Similarity Continued) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the expression for the ratios of areas of similar triangles. The proof of pythagoras theorem is also given. Illustrative examples are used for better understanding.

column5: रचनाएँ (Constructions): भाग 1/3 (Part 1/3) - Hindi
column7: This video is the first in a series of videos that deal with the topic of Constructions. This video explains the bisection of an angle, bisection of a line segment and the construction of an angle of 60 degrees measure. The underlying mathematical principles behind the constructions are explained in detail. A lot of animations are used to explain the actual constructions process.

column5: रचनाएँ (Constructions): भाग 2/3 (Part 2/3) - Hindi
column7:
This video explains how to construct the following:
1. A line parallel to a given straight line,
2. A triangle when the base, one base angle and sum of other two sides is given,
3. A triangle when the base, one base angle and the difference of other two sides is given,
4. A triangle when the perimeter and the base angles are given

column5: रचनाएँ (Constructions): भाग 3/3 (Part 3/3) - Hindi
column7:
This video explains the following constructions:
1. Division of a line segment using two methods
2. A triangle similar to a given triangle but scaled
3. Tangent to a circle

column5: द्विघात समीकरण(Quadratic Equations) - भाग १ (Part 1) - Hindi
column7: The video begins with a general expression of a quadratic equations. Examples is given to emphasize the importance of quadratic equations in real life. Identification of whether an equation is quadratic or not is explained using examples. Roots of equations are then discussed. Method of factorization to get the roots is discussed. The example discussed earlier to explain the motivation for the quadratic equations is finally solved.

column5: द्विघात समीकरण(Quadratic Equations) - भाग २ (Part 2) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the method of finding the roots of a quadratic equation by completing squares. Later on, the formula method is introduced. The nature of roots are discussed at the end of the video with the notion of discriminant being introduced simultaneously. Illustrative examples are distributed throughout the video.

column5: वृत्त (Circle) - Class 9 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video introduces the various terms related to circles like chord, diameter, etc. Various important theorems related to circles are covered. This video ends with a solved example covering the various concepts.

column5: वृत्त (Circle) - भाग २ (Part 2)
column7: This video continues to explore more theorems related to circles and chords. It also covers Cyclic Quadrilaterals and a few example problems on them.

column5: यूक्लिड की ज्यामिति कापरिचय (Introduction to Euclidean Geometry) - भाग १ (Part 1)
column7: Learn about the fundamentals of Geometry, the definitions of points, lines and surfaces. Also introduce yourself to Euclid's postulates.

column5: यूक्लिड की ज्यामिति कापरिचय (Introduction to Euclidean Geometry) - भाग २ (Part 2)
column7: Learn about a few more theorems and solve a few problems on Euclidean Geometry.

column5: समान्तर श्रेढ़ी (Arithmetic Progression)
column7: Learn about the concepts related to Arithmetic progression like common difference, Nth term of a series, and Sum of a series.

column5: सांख्यिकी भाग 1 (Statistics Part 1) - Class 10 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video teaches you how to find the mean of Ungrouped and Grouped data, as well as how to convert ungrouped data into grouped data. Example problems have been solved for better understanding.

column5: सांख्यिकी भाग 2 (Statistics Part 2) - Class 10 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video explains the Assumed Mean method, Step-Deviation method and Mode of grouped data.

column5: सांख्यिकी भाग 3 (Statistics Part 3) - Class 10 Maths - Hindi
column7: In this video, you will know what is the Median of Grouped data and how to find it, along with Cumulative Frequency Distribution and Ogive. You will also know in what circumstances should we use Mean, Median and Mode.

column5: चतुर्भुज भाग 1 (Quadrilaterals Part 1) - Class 9 Maths - Hindi
column7: In this video, you will learn what are quadrilaterals and their types, as well as the sum of angles of a quadrialteral and some properties of a Parallelogram.

column5: चतुर्भुज भाग 2 (Quadrilaterals Part 2) - Class 9 Maths - Hindi
column7: In this video, you will learn about more properties of a Parallelogram and solve a few proof questions.

column5: हमारे आस-पास के पदार्थ(Matter in our Surroundings) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान (Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: The video begins with the fundamental question of what is matter. The discussion then moves on to the particles that constitute matter. States of matter are then discussed and the properties of each state are discussed in detail and finally, the transitions between the states are discussed.

column5: जीवन की मौलिक इकाई(The Fundamental Unit of Life) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान(Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video, as the name suggests, is on the fundamental unit of life, i.e., the cell. Through representative images, the various constituents of a cell are explained in detail.

column5: कार्य (Work) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान (Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: The video first explains the importance of work by linking it to energy. It then explains the scientific meaning of work and gives methods of calculating work through various examples. The relation between the area under the force-displacement graph and work is then explained and the video ends with a few questions (tough ones) for the viewer to solve.

column5: बल तथा गति के नियम(Force and Laws of Motion) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान(Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video introduces the viewer to the concept of force and the associated terms. It then goes on to explain the first law of motion with the famous Coin on a Card experiment. Inertia is subsequently introduced. Momentum is then introduced with the second law and its conservation principle is explained. Finally, the video introduces the famous third law. Illustrative examples are scattered throughout the video to enhance understanding.

column5: गुरुत्वाकर्षण (Gravitation) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान (Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with the famous story of Newton and the apple and builds the motivation for the topic. Later on, gravitation is formally introduced mathematically and its various applications are discussed. The motion of a ball thrown from a height is studied in detail later on.

column5: ऊतक (Tissue) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान (Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: The video begins with a description of tissues. The difference between plant and animal tissues is later explained. The characteristics of various tissues are then explained in detail.

column5: हम बीमार क्यों होते हैं?(Why do we fall ill?): Part 1/2(भाग १/२) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान (Class 9 Science)
column7: This video gives the definition of health and then explains "Disease" in detail. The types and causes of diseases are explained and the difference between infectious and non-infectious diseases is given. The video ends with a classification of the various agents causing infectious diseases.

column5: हम बीमार क्यों होते हैं?(Why do we fall ill?): Part 2/2(भाग २/२) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान (Class 9 Science)
column7: This video begins with the general differences between the various disease causing organisms. The medium through which diseases are transmitted is then discussed. The symptoms of diseases are then explained. Later, principles of treatment and prevention are taken up. Vaccination is taken up at the end.

column5: प्राकृतिक संपदा (Natural Resources) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान (Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with a description of the three natural resources, namely land, water and air. Atmosphere and it's role are discussed followed by a discussion on winds and air pollution. Later, water is discussed with emphasis on the water cycle. Nitrogen cycle comes next. The video ends with a discussion on the ozone layer.

column5: क्या हमारे आस-पास केपदार्थ शुद्ध है ? (Is The Matter Around Us Pure?) - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान - Hindi
column7: This video begins with a description of homogeneous and heterogeneous mixtures. Methods of finding concentrations of solutions is explained with examples. Later on, suspension and colloids are explained as types of heterogenous mixtures. Tyndall effect in case of colloids is explained. Metals, non-metals and metalloids as different types of elements are then explained and their properties are listed.

column5: परमाणु की संरचना(Structure of an Atom) - भाग १ - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान(Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with a motivation for the topic. The question of the divisibility of an atom is then taken up. Later on various models for the structure of the atom, like Thomson's plum pudding model, Rutherford's model and Bohr's model are explained. Rutherford's famous alpha scattering experiment is also explained. The video ends with a discussion on subatomic particles, namely protons, electrons and neutrons. A summary of the discussion is given at the end.

column5: परमाणु की संरचना(Structure of an Atom) - भाग २ - कक्षा 9 विज्ञान(Class 9 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the concept of shells in the Bohr model and the rules for filling electrons in shells. Later on, the concepts of Atomic number, Mass number and valency are explained.

column5: जीवों में विविधता - भाग १(Diversity in Living Organisms - Part 1)
column7: This video explains the meaning of characteristics of living organisms and also the classification of organisms. The classification of organisms in groups like Monera, Protista, Fungii, Plantae and Animalia is explained.

column5: जीवों में विविधता - भाग २(Diversity in Living Organisms - Part 2)
column7: In this video, learn about the plantae kingdom. Learn about the various categories, thallophyta, bryophyta, pteridophyta, gymnosperms and angiosperms, and their characteristics.

column5: जीवों में विविधता - भाग ३(Diversity in Animals - Part 3)
column7: Learn about the kingdom Animalia and its phyla - Porifera, Coelentrata, Platyhelminthes, Nematoda and Annelida.

column5: जीवों में विविधता - भाग ४(Diversity in Animals - Part 4)
column7: Learn about the kingdom Animalia and its phyla - Arthropoda, Moluska, Echinodermata, Protochordata and Vertebrata.

column5: जीवों में विविधता - भाग ५(Diversity in Animals - Part 5)
column7: In this video, you will learn about Vertebrata phylum of kingdom animalia, and its classes Pisces, Amphibia, Reptilia, Aves and Mammals.

column5: गति (Motion) - भाग १
column7: Learn what is velocity and acceleration. Get familiar with the concepts of Constant and varying velocity. Also know about the importance of velocity and its uses in our daily lives.

column5: गति (Motion) - भाग २
column7: This video covers the graphical interpretation of speed, velocity and distance with respect to time, and also introduces the three laws of motion, along-with a demonstration of their derivation using the graphical method.

column5: गति (Motion) - भाग ३
column7: This video contains a few problems based on the use of the three Laws of Motion along with an explanation of their solution.

column5: परमाणु एवं अणु (Atoms and Molecules) - भाग १
column7: Learn about the concepts of atoms and molecules in this video. Laws of chemical reactions like the laws of conservation of mass and the law of constant proportions are discussed. Later Dalton's atomic theory is discussed. The video ends with a discussion on the symbols of elements according to the IUPAC conventions.

column5: खाद्य संसाधनों में सुधार(Improvement in Food Resources)
column7: Learn about food resources, improvement in farming methods, irrigation techniques, different types of crops, crop protection techniques, and culture of animals, chicken, fish and honey bees.

column5: विचरण और समानुपात(Variation and Proportion) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the lecture on Variation and Proportion for Class 8.

column5: परिमय तथा अपरिमय संख्या(Rational and Irrational Numbers) - कक्षा 8 गणित(Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the lecture on Rational and Irrational Numbers for Class 8.

column5: चतुर्भुज (Quadrilaterals) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the lecture on Quadrilaterals for class 8.

column5: सर्वसमिका: भाग 1/2 (Identities: Part 1/2) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the first part of the lecture on Identities for Class 8

column5: सर्वसमिका: भाग 2/2 (Identities: Part 2/2) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the second part of the lecture on Identities for Class 8

column5: घन और घन मूल (Cube and Cube Root) - कक्षा8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the lecture on Cube and Cube Roots for Class 8.

column5: क्षेत्रफल: भाग 1/2 (Area: Part 1/2) - कक्षा 8 गणित(Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is Part 1 of the lecture on 'Area' for Class 8.

column5: क्षेत्रफल: भाग 2/2 (Area: Part 2/2) - कक्षा 8 गणित(Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is Part 2 of the lecture on 'Area' for Class 8.

column5: चक्रवृद्धि ब्याज(Compound Interest) - Class 8 Math (कक्षा 8 गणित) - Hindi
column7: This is a video on Compound Interest for Class 8 Math.

column5: वर्ग और वर्गमूल (Square and Square Root) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the video on Squares and Square Roots for Class 8.

column5: वृत्त (Circle) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the video on Circles for class 8 Maths. It explains some basic theorems and illustrates their applications through relevant examples.

column5: समान्तर रेखाएं (Parallel Lines) - कक्षा 8 गणित(Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the video on Parallel lines for class 8 Math. It illustrates important concepts and properties related to parallel lines with illustrative examples.

column5: एक चर वाले समीकरण(Equations in One Variable) - कक्षा 8 गणित(Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the video explaining the important class of equations having one variable for class 8 Math.Through various illustrative examples and word problems, the method of solving such equations is explained and verification of the solution is also illustrated.

column5: घनफल तथा पृष्ठीय क्षेत्रफल(Volume and Surface Area) - कक्षा 8 गणित(Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This chapter explains the surface area and volume of three common solid shapes namely, Sphere, Cylinder and Cone. Illustrative examples are used to demonstrate the calculations.

column5: Statistics (सांख्यिकी) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This video takes up the chapter on Statistics for class 8 Math. It explains the basic statistical concepts like frequency, mean, tally marks etc. through various examples.

column5: आँकड़ों का प्रबंधन (Data Handling) - कक्षा 8 गणित(Class 8 Maths) - Hindi
column7: The video explains the various methods of organizing data. The methods covered are pictograph, bar graph, double bar graph, frequency table and pie chart. Chance and probability are explained at the end.

column5: चतुर्भुजों की रचना(Constructions of Quadrilaterals) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This is the video that demonstrates the construction of quadrilaterals for various sets of available data.

column5: घातांक (Indices) - कक्षा 8 गणित (Class 8 Math) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with a recap of squares, square roots, cube and cube roots. Indices in various forms are later introduced. The various laws of indices are explained. Special emphasis is given to the index 0. The video ends with an example showing the application of the various laws of indices.

column5: पूर्णांक (Integers) - कक्षा ७गणित (Class 7 Maths) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with a differentiation between integers and whole numbers. Negative integers are then explained. Method of representing integers on number line is explained. The concept of additive inverse is then taken up. Addition, subtraction and multiplication of integers is taken up with suitable examples.

column5: प्रायोगिक ज्यामिति(Practical Geometry)
column7: Learn how to construct a quadrilateral when you are given any 5 quantities (5 lengths, or 4 lengths and 1 angle, 3 lengths 2 angles, or even 2 lengths and 3 angles).

column5: कुछ प्राकृतिक परिघटनाएँ(Some Natural Calamities) - कक्षा 8 विज्ञान (Class 8 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with lightning and explains the principles of electrostatics that cause lightning. It then explains the safety measures that can be followed in case a lightning strike is expected. The next calamity discussed is earthquake and the safety measures to be employed in case of an earthquake.

column5: कोयला और पेट्रोलियम(Coal and Petroleum) - कक्षा 8 विज्ञान (Class 8 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video begins with examples of utilities of coal and petroleum in real life. The process of formation of these natural resources is explained. The difference between renewable and non-renewable natural resources is explained. Refining of petroleum is explained. The need to conserve these resources is discussed and some methods to conserve these resources are given.

column5: घर्षण (Friction) - कक्षा 8 विज्ञान (Class 8 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video explains the concept of friction. The difference between static and kinetic friction is explained. The advantages and disadvantages of friction are listed out. Situations where it will be desirable to increase or reduce friction are shown. The concept of rolling friction is introduced, ad its benefits are explained and the video finally ends with the concept of fluid friction.

column5: फसल उत्पादन एवं प्रबंध(Crop Production and Management) - कक्षा 8 विज्ञान (Class 8 Science) - Hindi
column7: This video covers the various agricultural operations, right from ploughing to final harvesting and storage. It gives an overview of the various processes, their importance, and the tools used. Types of crops are also explained.

column5: ध्वनि (Sound) - कक्षा 8 विज्ञान (Class 8 Science) - Hindi
column7: The various aspect of sound, right from the generation, propagation, to noise pollution and methods to control it are covered in this video. The elements of the human ear are shown and how the ear perceives sound is explained. The important parts of a sound wave, frequency, amplitude etc. and the way they affect our perception of sound is discussed.

column5: सूक्ष्मजीव - मित्र एवं शत्रु १/२(Microorganisms - Friend and Foe 1/2) - Class 8 Science - Hindi
column7: This video introduces the viewer to microorganisms. Types of microorganisms, their uses (commercial, medicinal, environmental etc.) are discussed.

column5: सूक्ष्मजीव - मित्र एवं शत्रु २/२(Microorganisms - Friend and Foe 2/2) - Class 8 Science - Hindi
column7: This video focusses on the harm caused by micro-organisms. Various diseases and modes of disease transmission are discussed. Methods of preservation of food using common preservatives like salt, sugar, vinegar etc. is discussed. Pasteurization of milk is covered at the end.

column5: दहन और ज्वाला(Combustion and Flames) - Class 8 Science - Hindi
column7: This video explains concepts like combustion, ignition temperature, types of combustion, different regions of a flame, harmful products of flame, etc.

column5: वायु तथा जल प्रदूषण (Air and Water Pollution) - Class 8 Science - Hindi
column7: This video explains concepts related to air and water pollution. Case studies of Taj Mahal and Ganga river are taken up. Ozone depletion, greenhouse effect etc. are explained. Methods of controlling air and water pollution are explained.

column5: किशोरावस्था(Adolescence) - Class 8 Science - Hindi
column7: This video covers various aspects related to adolescence. The various types of changes experienced, physical, hormonal etc. are explained. The development of reproductive organs is explained. The reason for periods in females is explained. The video ends with a discussion on the importance of maintaining health and hygiene during adolescence and encourages the viewers to abstain from drug abuse.

column5: तारे एवं सौर परिवार (Stars and the Solar System) - Class 8 Science - Hindi
column7: This video gives information of various celestial bodies, beginning with the moon and covers stars, planets, constellations, comets, meteors etc. Information on the lunar cycle is given and important characteristics of celestial bodies are described.

column5: प्रकाश (Light)
column7: This video covers concepts of types of rays, rules of reflection and its types, the human eye as well as the kaleidoscope.

column5: क्षेत्रमिति - भाग १/३(Mensuration - Part 1/3)
column7: In this video, the perimeter and area of basic shapes like triangle, rectangle and circle are explained and some solved examples are shown for better understanding.

column5: क्षेत्रमिति - भाग २/३(Mensuration - Part 2/3)
column7: In this video, learn about surface area of 3D objects like cone and cylinder.

column5: क्षेत्रमिति - भाग ३/३(Mensuration - Part 3/3) - कक्षा ७ गणित(Class 7 Maths) - Hindi
column7: Learn what is the Volume of 3D figures like Cube, Cuboid, Cone and Cylinder. Also, learn how to solve a few interesting example problems on this chapter.

column5: त्रिभुजों की सर्वांगसमता(Congruence of Triangles)
column7: Learn about the meaning of congruence and the various tests for congruence of triangles, like SSS, SAS, ASA test etc.

column5: परिमेय संख्या (Rational Numbers)
column7: Know what is a rational number and how to visualize them on a number line.

column5: प्रायोगिक ज्यामिति - भाग१/३ (Practical Geometry - Part 1/3)
column7: Learn how to construct a parallel line and triangles using the SSS, SAS, ASA rule.

column5: प्रायोगिक ज्यामिति - भाग२/३ (Practical Geometry - Part 2/3)
column7: Learn how to construct triangles for the SAS rule, ASA rule and RHS rule, along-with examples.

column5: बीजीय व्यंजक (Algebraic Expression)
column7: In this video, you will learn about constants and variables, how they form algebraic expressions, coefficient of algebraic terms as well as addition and subtraction of algebraic expressions.

column5: बीजीय व्यंजक भाग 1 (Algebraic Expression Part 1) - कक्षा ७ गणित(Class 7 Maths) - Hindi
column7: In this video, you will learn about constants and variables, how they form algebraic expressions, coefficient of algebraic terms as well as addition and subtraction of algebraic expressions.

column5: बीजीय व्यंजक भाग 2 (Algebraic Expression Part 2) - कक्षा ७ गणित(Class 7 Maths) - Hindi
column7: In this video you will learn about the types of expressions, how to find the value of an expression as well as the applications of algebraic expressions.

column5: त्रिभुज और उसके गुण भाग १(Triangles And Its Properties Part 1) - Class 7 Maths - Hindi
column7: In this video you will learn about: - Triangles and their types - Median of triangle - Altitude of a triangle - External angle and its properties - Sum of internal angles of a triangle

column5: त्रिभुज और उसके गुण भाग २(Triangles And Its Properties Part 2) - Class 7 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video will introduce to various types of triangles like Equilateral, Isosceles and Right-angled triangle. It also covers Triangle summation theorem and the Pythagoras theorem, along with solved examples.

column5: रेखा एवं कोण (Lines and Angles) - Class 7 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video tells you what is a Line, Line Segment and a Ray. It also talks about the different Pairs of Angles and Pairs of Lines, with solved examples.

column5: बीजीय व्यंजक भाग 1 (Algebraic Expression Part 1) - कक्षा ७ गणित(Class 7 Maths) - Hindi
column7: In this video, you will learn about constants and variables, how they form algebraic expressions, coefficient of algebraic terms as well as addition and subtraction of algebraic expressions.

column5: बीजीय व्यंजक भाग 2 (Algebraic Expression Part 2) - कक्षा ७ गणित(Class 7 Maths) - Hindi
column7: In this video you will learn about the types of expressions, how to find the value of an expression as well as the applications of algebraic expressions.

column5: त्रिभुज और उसके गुण भाग १(Triangles And Its Properties Part 1) - Class 7 Maths - Hindi
column7: In this video you will learn about: - Triangles and their types - Median of triangle - Altitude of a triangle - External angle and its properties - Sum of internal angles of a triangle

column5: त्रिभुज और उसके गुण भाग २(Triangles And Its Properties Part 2) - Class 7 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video will introduce to various types of triangles like Equilateral, Isosceles and Right-angled triangle. It also covers Triangle summation theorem and the Pythagoras theorem, along with solved examples.

column5: रेखा एवं कोण (Lines and Angles) - Class 7 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video tells you what is a Line, Line Segment and a Ray. It also talks about the different Pairs of Angles and Pairs of Lines, with solved examples.

column5: आँकड़ो का संग्रह भाग १ (Data Handling Part 1) - Class 7 Maths - Hindi
column7: This video tells you about Collection of Data and its arrangement with solved examples. It also talks about the average of given data.

column5: Magical Lighting of a Candle (मोमबत्ती को जादुईतरीके से जलाना)
column7: This experiment shows a novel way of lighting a candle. It's a cool party trick that will amaze your friends.

column5: Inflating a Balloon using Chemical Reaction (गुब्बारे कोरासायनिक प्रतिक्रिया सेफुलाना )
column7: This experiment shows how, with proper arrangement, the gas evolving from a chemical reaction can be used to inflate a balloon.

column5: Effect of Soap on Water Surface (पानी कीसतह पर साबुन का असर)
column7: Observe the magic when you dip a soap-covered finger in water. And understand a new form of force, Surface Tension.

column5: Gravity Defying Water (गुरुत्वाकर्षण का पालन नाकरने वाला पानी)
column7: This video demonstrates a cool trick which is a visual treat. The concepts of atmospheric pressure and pressure-volume relationship are explained.

column5: Siphon (साइफन)
column7: This video demonstrates the working of a siphon.

column5: Effect of Air Pressure on Water Level (जल स्तरपर वायु के दबाव का प्रभाव)
column7: This video demonstrates a trick to raise the water level in a glass using just a candle. The concepts of Air Pressure and Vacuum due to Combustion are explained.

column5: डायाफ्राम का सिद्धांत(Principle of Diaphragm)
column7: Learn how we draw air into our lungs with the help of our diaphragm and understand the principle behind it using a simple setup with balloons.

column5: होवेर्क्राफ्ट की कार्य प्रणाली(Working of a Hovercraft)
column7: In this video, you will understand how a hovercraft works and the principles of air pressure and Newton's third law behind this.

column5: पशुओं के बारे में दिलचस्पतथ्य (Interesting Facts about Animals)
column7: In this video, learn about various interesting and astounding facts about animal species, covering both marine and land animals. This video is for general knowledge and not a part of school syllabus for any board.

column5: ब्रम्हांड से जुड़े कुछ दिलचस्पतथ्य (Interesting Facts About The Universe)
column7: Learn about various fun facts and concepts about Earth, the Sun, our Solar System as well as other elements in space. This video is for general knowledge and not a part of school syllabus for any board.

column5: चाँद की कलाएं (Phases of Moon)
column7: In this video, you will get to learn why the moon appears differently on different nights, why it is a periodic phenomenon and the phases of the moon. This video is for general knowledge and not a part of school syllabus for any board.

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 0 (भाग 0)
column7: This is the introductory video of OLI's English course. A major part of the video explains the method in which the course will be conducted and builds the motivation of the student. However, this video is not without it's share of content. The latter half of the video focusses on the part which will be needed most in the course - Asking questions in English.

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 1 (भाग 1) - Parts of Speech
column7: The English course formally begins with this video. In this video, we begin studying English Grammar, with the first lecture being Parts of Speech. All parts of speech are introduced with the help of a poem whose original source can be found here: http://www.happychild.org.uk/acc/tpr/...

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 2 (भाग 2) - Types of Nouns
column7: This video takes up the first part of speech, i.e. Noun. It introduces the types of nouns with illustrative examples. The lecture if followed by a short quiz at the end.

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 3 (भाग 3) - Nouns: Gender
column7: This video explains the concept of Gender and also explains the similarity and differences between the notion of Gender in Hindi and English. It provides illustrative examples for the students to understand this concept. The answers to the short quiz conducted at the end of the previous lecture are also discussed at the end of this lecture.

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 4 (भाग 4) - Nouns: Number
column7: This video introduces the notions of singular and plural nouns. A large amount of the video is focussed on the methods of converting the singular of commonly used words to plural. A systematic approach is used for the same. The video ends with a short quiz to test the concepts of the students.

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 5 (भाग 5) - Types of Adjectives
column7: This video explains the five types of adjectives, namely, qualitative, quantitative, numeral, demonstrative and interrogative with the sub-types. All the types are discussed in details with illustrative examples. Some common greetings are discussed as a part of this lectures' "miscellaneous things". The video ends with solutions to the questions asked in the previous video.

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 6 (भाग 6)
column7: This video explains the three degrees of comparison, namely positive, comparative and superlative. Methods of converting the positive degree to comparative and superlative are explained. Some common colors are covered in the "Miscellaneous" section of this video.

column5: Learn English (अंग्रेजीसीखें) - Part 7 (भाग 7) - Articles
column7: This video explains about articles, their two types - definite and indefinite, and also when to use them and how. The miscellaneous section in this video covers cardinals and ordinals.

column5: വൃത്തം (Circles) - ഭാഗം൧ (Part 1)
column7: Learn about properties of angles, lines and triangles inscribed in a circle, along with a descriptive derivation of these properties.

column5: വൃത്തം (Circles) - ഭാഗം൨ (Part 2)
column7: Learn about the relationship between angles subtended at the center and at the edge of a circle along-with its derivation.

column5: വൃത്തം (Circles) - ഭാഗം൩ (Part 3)
column7: Learn about a few theorems on lengths of sides and arcs when figures are inscribed in a circle, along-with their proofs.

column5: സ്പർശരേഖ (Tangents)
column7: Learn what are tangents to a curve. the properties of tangents to a circle, how to construct tangents to a circle from a given point, as well as about incentres an incircles of a triangle.

column5: വൈദ്യുതപ്രവാഹത്തിന്റെതാപ ഫലങ്ങള് (Thermal Effects of Electric Current) - Class 10 - Malayalam
column7: The video begins with motivation for the topic, citing examples from real life where thermal effects of electric current are used to do useful things. The thermal effects of electric current are then formally and briefly discussed. Joule's law is introduced with details of the experiments that led to the law. The equations for Joule's law have been discussed in this video.

column5: വൈദ്യുതപ്രവാഹത്തിന്റെരാസഫലങ്ങൾ(Chemical Effects of Electric Current) - Class 10 - Malayalam
column7: This video discusses the commonly sighted and commercially important phenomenon like electrolysis, displacement of a metal from its salt solution, electroplating etc. Theory for these phenomenon has been deeply covered in this video.

column5: A.C.ജനറേറ്റര്‍ (A.C. Generator) - Class 10 Science - Malayalam
column7: This video explains the process of generating alternating current with proper graphs and illustrations.

column5: വൈദ്യുത ശക്തി(Electric Power) - Class 10 Science - Malayalam
column7: This video explains the concept of power. It then explains safety fuses and also electric light sources.

column5: വൈദ്യുതകാന്തികപ്രേരണം(Electromagnetic Induction) - Class 10 Science - Malayalam
column7: This video explains Electromagnetic Induction and its applications. The science behind this phenomenon is explained and graphical representations are used for better understanding.

column5: വൈദ്യുതപവർഉല്പാദനവും വിതരണവും(Electric Power Generation and Distribution) - Malayam
column7: In this video, the generation of power and its transmission to the households is explained. Three phase networks, series parallel connections etc. are explained. Certain daily appliances and their pin configurations are explained. The video ends with the energy unit (kWh) and its calculation.

column5: ആസിഡ് ആന്‍ഡ്‌ ആൽകലി (Acid and Alkali) - Part 1 - Class 10 - Malayalam
column7: This video begins with an introduction to acids encountered in daily life. Indicators are then discussed, with focus on litmus and phenolphthalein. The common acids, like hydrochloric acid, sulphuric acid etc. are discussed. Similarly, common bases like sodium hydroxide, magnesium hydroxide etc.are discussed. The utility of magnesium hydroxide as an antacid is explained. The video ends with information of acids found in products used daily, like lemon, curd etc.

column5: ആസിഡുകൾ & ആൽക്കലി (Acids and Alkali) - Part 2 - Class 10 - Malayalam
column7: This video covers acids and bases in detail. Indicators, pH scale, salts etc. are covered in detail. Ionic equations are also explained.

column5: ഊർജ പരിപാലനം - ഭാഗം 1(Energy Conservation - Part 1)
column7: This video discusses combustion and various fossil fuels like coal, CNG, LPG etc. The process of formation of fossil fuels is explained, and the concept of fuel efficiency is discussed. Later on, biomass and biogas are discussed.

column5: धातू आणि अ-धातू  (Metals and Non-metals) - इयत्ता10 वी विज्ञान (Class 10 Science)
column7: This video is the first part in the lecture series on Metals and Non-Metals for Class X in Marathi.

column5: जादू: रासायनिकअभिक्रियांची (Magic of Chemical Reactions) - इयत्ता 10 वी विज्ञान (Class 10 Science)
column7: This video begins with a comparison between physical and chemical changes. The need for representing reactions using concise equations and the balancing of chemical equations is then explained. The different types of reactions are then explained. Rancidity in oil is finally taken up and methods to avoid it are explained.

column5: रसायन आम्ल आम्लारीचे(Acid Base Reactions) - भाग १ - इयत्ता 10 वी विज्ञान(Class 10 Science)
column7: This video begins with a discussion on indicators.. Later on, the pH scale is explained. This is followed by a discussion on the importance of acids and bases in our body and surroundings. Later on, reactions of acids with metals, metal oxides, metal carbonates and bases. Ionization is then explained and the neutralization reaction is thus explored in greater depth.

column5: रसायन आम्ल आम्लारीचे(Acid Base Reactions) - भाग २ - इयत्ता 10 वी विज्ञान(Class 10 Science)
column7: This video covers some common salts that have a great utility in our daily lives. Common salt (NaCl), Sodium bicarbonate (baking soda), sodium carbonate, bleaching powder, etc. are covered. The process of saponification, or soap formation, is covered at the end.

column5: सर्व काही विद्युत चुंबकाविषयी(Magnetic Effects of Electric Current): भाग 1
column7: This video explains various concepts like magnetic field lines and their properties, field generated by a solenoid, field generated by a current carrying wire, Right Hand Thumb Rule and Fleming's Left Hand Rule.

column5: अद्भुत जग कार्बनी संयुगा(Carbon and its Compounds) - भाग १/३
column7: Learn about saturated and unsaturated hydrocarbons, double and triple bonds, catenation, allotropes of carbon like graphite,diamond etc., their uses, branched hydrocarbons and finally benzene, in this video.

column5: अद्भुत जग कार्बनी संयुगा(Carbon and its Compounds) - भाग २/३
column7: Learn about nomenclature of various carbon compounds like alkanes, alkenes and alkynes with functional groups like hallides, hydroxyl, ketone and aldehyde. Also learn about homologous organic compounds.

column5: ओढ : पृथ्वीची: भाग १ (The Pull of the Earth: Part 1)
column7: Learn what is gravity, Newton's law of gravitation, Earth's gravitation force and acceleration and how this causes high and low tides.

column5: ओढ : पृथ्वीची: भाग २ (The Pull of the Earth: Part 2)
column7: Get to know what is the value of g, and how it varies with height and depth from the surface of the earth, as well as due to the uneven shape of the earth. Also learn about mass, weight and free fall.

column5: आम्ल, आम्लारी व क्षार : भाग १ (Acid, Bases and Salt : Part 1) - Class 9 Science - Marathi
column7: Learn the classification of Acid, Bases and Salt. Know what is the pH of a solution and many more!

column5: वर्ग आणि वर्गमूळ (Squares and Square Roots)
column7: Learn how to find the square root of whole numbers as well as decimal numbers.

column5: घन आणि घनमूळ (Cubes and Cube Roots)
column7: This video covers the topics of cubes of whole numbers, perfect cubes, cube roots, and how to find the cube root of a perfect cube. It also tells us about the specialty of the Taxi number.

column5: बहुपदी (Polynomials) - Class 8 Maths - Marathi
column7: In this video, you will learn what Polynomials are, their types, as well as the degree of a polynomial.

column5: बहुपादींचा भागाकार भाग १(Division of Polynomials) - Class 8 Maths - Marathi
column7: In this video you will learn how to divide a polynomial with another, with a few solved examples.

column5: घातांक (Exponents) - Class 8 Maths - Marathi
column7: In this video, you will learn what Exponents and laws of exponents. You will also learn how to use these laws on Fractional exponents

column5: एकचल समीकरणे (Equations in One Variable) - Class 8 Maths - Marathi
column7: In this video, we get to learn how to identify equations in one variable and how to solve the equation. We have also discussed examples where these equations can be used.

column5: विद्युत्प्रवाह (Electricity) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: In this video, you will learn about the function of electric current and types of electrolysis as well as the concepts of magnetic field of flux and electromagnetic induction.

column5: प्रकाशाचे परावर्तन(Reflection of Light) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video introduces reflection of light and explains it's laws. Properties of image, and types of reflection are explained. Interesting phenomenon like multiple reflections, infinite images etc. are taken up. The video ends with the explanation of an important product based on the principles of reflection: Periscope.

column5: तारे व आपली सूर्यमाला(Stars and our Solar System) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video takes you through a tour of the various planets, constellations and other celestial bodies like asteroids, meteors, comets etc. Artificial satellites are discussed and the work done by Indian Space Research Organization (ISRO) is explained. Lunar cycle is also discussed. It is an interesting video to watch and a visual delight.

column5: चुंबकत्व (Magnetism) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video introduces magnetism. Concepts like types of magnets, poles, magnetic force etc. are introduced. Further, the uses of magnetism are explained.

column5: ऊर्जेचे स्रोत (Sources of Energy) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video covers all types of energy sources, renewable as well as non-renewable. The problems with conventional energy sources and the measures taken to control them are also explained.

column5: पेशीरचना व सूक्ष्मजीव(Structure of Cells and Microorganisms) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video gives a description of the various parts of a cell, like nucleus, mitochondria, golgi apparatus etc. The functions of each of these parts is explained. Later on, various types of microorganisms like algae, bacteria, fungus, virus etc. are discussed and the uses of these microorganisms and also the harm they inflict on humans is explained.

column5: हवा (Air) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video covers the composition of the atmosphere and details about each constituent. Topics like methods of producing oxygen in the air, fixation of nitrogen, uses of inert gases etc. are covered. Air pollution is taken up later and laws and solutions for tackling air pollution are discussed. The video ends with a discussion on the role of an observatory.

column5: रोग (Disease) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video begins with a motivation for the topic. Later diseases are classified in various types. Some important diseases like polio, chicken pox, rabies etc. are covered in detail with their symptoms explained and their causes and prevention methods enlisted and their cures discussed. The video ends with a discussion on AIDS.

column5: जैविक विविधता(Biodiversity) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: The variety observed in living organisms is explained in this video. Also, the factors causing a reduction in the diversity are explained. Methods to preserve and protect the biodiversity are also discussed.

column5: मृदा (Soil) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: In this video, soil and its properties and uses are explained. Types of soil are discussed. The process of soil formation is explained. Soil erosion and methods to control it are explained. Finally, soil pollution and soil testing are discussed.

column5: पशुसंगोपन (Animal Husbandry) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video begins with the uses of animals in our daily lives. Various aspects related to animal husbandry like shelter, food and health of animals are covered. The use of cross-breed strains for increasing productivity is discussed. Later on, occupations complementary to agriculture are taken up, like poultry farming, sericulture, pisciculture etc.

column5: शेती (Agriculture) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: This video covers the different aspects of agriculture and gives details about the different operations involved. The tools used for agriculture are discussed. The video ends with a discussion on tissue culture.

column5: अणूची संरचना (Structure of Atoms) - Class 8 Science - Marathi
column7: In this video, the various theories related to the structure of atom, like Dalton's atomic theory, Thomson's model, Rutherford's model are explained. Subatomic particles like protons, electrons, neutrons and their properties are explained. Concepts like atomic number, mass number, valency, isotope etc. are introduced.

column5: रासायनिक अभिक्रिया आणित्यांचे प्रकार (Chemical Reactions & their Types)
column7: This video covers defines chemical reactions and covers their various types like displacement reactions, combination reactions, oxidation reactions etc. Role of catalyst and heat in a chemical reaction is also discussed.

column5: धातू आणि अधातू : भाग १/२(Metals and Non-Metals : Part 1/2)
column7: Learn about Metals and Non-Metals and understand how to differentiate them based on properties like ductility, lustre, conductivity, sonority etc.

column5: धातू आणि अधातू : भाग २/२(Metals and Non-Metals : Part 2/2)
column7: In this video, you will learn about the chemical reactions and uses of metals and non-metals, as well as the concepts of noble metals, rusting and alloy.

column5: पदार्थाची गुणवैशिष्ट्ये(Properties of Substances)
column7: Learn about the three states of matter, Solid, Liquid and Gas, and their transition from one state to another. Also learn about processes like Evaporation, Condensation, Freezing and Distillation.

column5: वातावरणीय दाब(Atmospheric Pressure)
column7: Learn about atmospheric pressure and its importance in our daily life, along with the examples of how a few daily life mechanisms work using the principles of pressure.

column5: ଦ୍ୱିଘାତ ସମୀକରଣ(Quadratic Equations): Part 1/3 - Odia Maths
column7: This video is on 'Quadratic Polynomials'. It explains quadratic polynomials, quadratic equation, and their roots. It also throws light on finding the roots and their few properties

column5: ଦ୍ୱିଘାତ ସମୀକରଣ(Quadratic Equations): Part 2/3 - Odia Maths
column7: This video explains the discriminant of a quadratic equation and its significance. The nature of roots for various signs of the discriminant is explained and in the end, roots are expressed as a function of the discriminant.

column5: ଦ୍ୱିଘାତ ସମୀକରଣ(Quadratic Equations): Part 3/3 - Odia Maths
column7: This video demonstrates how a few higher order polynomials can be reduced to quadratic equations by proper substitution.

column5: ସମ୍ଭାବ୍ୟତା (Probability) - Part 1 - Odia Maths
column7: This video begins with a motivational examples explaining the importance of Probability in real life. Later on, various important concepts like sample space, set, event, theoretical and empirical probability etc. are explained with illustrative examples.

column5: ସମ୍ଭାବ୍ୟତା (Probability) - Part 2 - Odia Maths
column7: This video begins with a definition of set, sample space and events. Later on, types of events, like compound events, mutually exclusive events are explained. Finding the probability of an event is explained with examples. At the end, the method of finding the probability of union of events is explained.

column5: କମ୍ପ୍ୟୁଟର (Computers) - Odia Maths
column7: The video explains the various parts of a computer and later, decimal to binary and binary to decimal conversion is explained.

column5: ବୃତ୍ତ ର କ୍ଷେତ୍ରଫଳ (Area of a Circle)
column7: This video begins explains the formula for the area of a circle and builds the intuition for it by relating it to the area of a rectangle. Later, areas of annular regions, sectors and segments are explained with illustrative examples.

column5: ବିଦ୍ୟୁତ (Electricity): Part 1/3 - Odia Science
column7: This video explains electric current and charge and the relation between them. A basic circuit is then explained and the flow of current is discussed. Basic electrical symbols are then explained.

column5: ବିଦ୍ୟୁତ (Electricity): Part 2/3 - Odia Science
column7: The video begins with a discussion of electronic charge and then electric potential is discussed. After that, the Ohm's Law is discussed and the concept of resistance is introduced.

column5: ରାସା୍ୟନିକ ପ୍ରତିକ୍ରିୟା ଓରାସାୟନିକ ସମୀକରଣ(Chemical Reactions and Equations) - Odia Science
column7: This video teaches how to write and balance a chemical equation. The different types of reactions are explained and topics like corrosion, and rancidity are also taken up.

column5: ଅମ୍ଳ କ୍ଷରକ ଓ ଲବଣ(Acids Bases and Salts) - Odia Science
column7: Learn what are acids, bases and salts as well as how to distinguish between them using physical and chemical tests, as well as indicators.

column5: ମୌଳିକ ଗୁ୍ଡିକର ପର୍ଯ୍ୟାୟ(Periodic Classification of Elements)
column7: Learn about the evolution of the periodic table from Dobereiner's triads, Newland's Octave, Mendeleev's periodic table to finally the modern periodic table.

column5: ଧାତୁ ଓ ଅଧାତୁ (Metals and Non metals)
column7: Learn what are metals and non metals, and how to differentiate between them based on their physical properties like Lustre, Ductility and Malleability along-with examples.

column5: இயக்கம் (Motion) - பாகம் 1/3 (Part 1/3)
column7: In this video, types of motion, difference between distance and displacement and the difference between speed and velocity and the concept of acceleration are covered.

column5: இயக்கம் (Motion) - பாகம் 2/3 (Part 2/3)
column7: In this video, graphical representation of distance, displacement and velocity is covered.

column5: இயக்கம் (Motion) - பாகம் 3/3 (Part 3/3)
column7: Learn about equations of motion and their derivation using graphical methods in this final video on the topic motion.

column5: அணு அமைப்பு (Atomic Structure)
column7: In this video, the atomic models like Rutherford's model, Bohr's model etc. are explained. Concepts like atomic number, mass number, isotopes etc. are explained.

column5: எண் அமைப்பு - பாகம்1/2 (Number System - Part 1/2) - Class 9 Maths - Tamil
column7: Types of numbers, natural, whole, integers etc. are explained. Expressing rational numbers in decimal form is also taken up.Taught by: Kartik Vignesh

column5: எண் அமைப்பு - பாகம்2/2 (Number System - Part 2/2) - Class 9 Maths - Tamil
column7: This video takes up irrational and real numbers. The method of plotting irrational numbers on the real number line is explained.

column5: வடிவியல்ஒருங்கிணைக்க(Coordinate Geometry) - Class 9 Maths - Tamil
column7: This video explains coordinate geometry, primarily Cartesian Coordinate system. Concepts of coordinates of a point, quadrants, etc. are discussed. Plotting a point on the coordinate plane is explained with examples and method of calculating the distance between two points is explained.

column5: வடிவியல் - பாகம் 1/2 (Geometry - Part 1/2) - Class 9 Maths - Tamil
column7: This video explains the basic concepts of geometry like parallel lines, acute/ obtuse angles, transversals, complementary/ supplementary angles etc.

column5: வடிவியல் - பாகம் 2/2 (Geometry - Part 2/2) - Class 9 Maths - Tamil
column7: This video covers congruence of triangles and the tests for congruence. An illustrative example is given at the end that covers many of the concepts covered in this chapter.

column5: నిరూపక జ్యామితి (Co-ordinate Geometry) - భాగం ౧/౩ (Part 1/3)
column7: In this video, the motivation for the chapter is built and the axes and quadrants are defined.

column5: నిరూపక జ్యామితి (Co-ordinate Geometry) - భాగం ౨/౩ (Part 2/3)
column7: Learn how to calculate the distance between two points A and B on the coordinate plane and the section formula for dividing a line into two parts.

column5: నిరూపక జ్యామితి (Co-ordinate Geometry) - భాగం ౩/౩ (Part 3/3)
column7: Learn how to find the centroid and area of a given triangle, and the slope of a given line. Also learn how to determine collinearity of three points using different methods.

column5: చలనం పార్ట్ ౧/౨(Motion Part 1/2)
column7: Learn about the basic concepts of speed, velocity, relative motion and also how to calculate the average velocity for a certain path.

column5: చలనం పార్ట్ ౨/౨(Motion Part 2/2)
column7: Learn about direction of velocity and acceleration. Also get familiar with the three Newton's Laws of Motion, with explanation of the proof of each law.

column5: వృత్తాలు (Circles) - భాగం ౧/౨
column7: Learn about about circles and their various parts like radius, diameter, chord, arc, sector etc.

column5: రసాయన బంధం పార్ట్ ౧(Chemical Bonding Part 1) - Class 10 - Telugu Science
column7: In this video, you will learn about Chemical Bond formation, Lewis Dot Structure, the Octet rule, as well as what is a chemical bond and its types.

column5: రసాయన బంధం పార్ట్ ౨(Chemical Bonding Part 2) - Class 10 - Telugu Science
column7: In this video you will learn about Ionic Bonds and the Formation of Ionic bonds.

column5: బీజీయ సమాసాలు(Algebraic Expressions) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This is the video on algebraic expressions for class 7. This is based on the syllabus of Andhra Pradesh Board.

column5: చతుర్భుజాలు(Quadrilaterals) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This video explains the concept of a quadrilateral and covers the details of various common quadrilaterals like parallelograms, rhombus, kite etc. The video is based on Andhra Pradesh State Board syllabus.

column5: కోణాలు మరియు వాటిలక్షణాలు (Angles and their Characteristics) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: The video begins with the conversion of angles from degrees to radians and vice versa. The concepts of complementary and supplementary angles are then explained. Vertically opposite angles are then explained. The concepts of a transverse of two parallel lines and corresponding , alternating and interior angles are explained. The video ends with some illustrative examples and the process of measurements of angles using a protractor.

column5: సామాన్య సమీకరణాలు(Simple Equations) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This is an interactive video based on the chapter 3 of Class 7 of the Andhra Pradesh board syllabus.

column5: దత్తాంశ నిర్వహణ (Data Handling) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: The video begins with an introduction of the chapter. This is followed by a discussion on mean, mode and median. After that, bar graphs and pie charts are discussed. Illustrative examples are included for better understanding.

column5: ఘాతాంకాలు(Exponents) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This video begins with a motivation for the need of exponents. After that, important terminologies related to exponents are explained. Writing a number in the exponential form is then taught. Prime factorization as a method to do the same is discussed. The various laws of exponents are then discussed with examples. The video ends with a summary of the various concepts taught.

column5: వైశాల్యం - చుట్టుకొలత(Area and Perimeter) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This video begins with the area of a parallelogram. The correlation between parallelogram area and rectangle area is explained. Later, the areas of triangle and rhombus are discussed. After that, area and circumference of a circle are discussed. Illustrative problems are solved for better understanding. The video ends with a summary of all the formulae.

column5: త్రిభుజాలసర్వసమానత్వం(Congruence of Triangles) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: The video begins with a motivation for the topic and explains the difference between congruence and similarity. Later, congruence of line segments is explained. This is followed by congruence of triangles and the various tests for congruence, like SSS test, etc. are explained with examples.

column5: పూర్ణ సంఖ్యలు (Integers) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This video introduces integers and the basic operations of addition, subtraction, division and multiplication that are performed on integers.

column5: త్రిభుజము ధర్మాలు(Properties of Triangles) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This video begins with an introduction to the types of triangles. The relation between the sides of the triangles is later explained. The centroid is defined and explained. Later on, two important theorems, one concerning the sum of angles of a triangle, and the other concerning the external angle property were discussed. An example problem is solved at the end.

column5: త్రిమితీయ మరియుద్విమితీయ ఆకారాలుఅవగాహన(Understanding 2D and 3D Shapes) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This video begins with an introduction to the various 2D and 3D shapes encountered daily. Later 3D nets, and also the cross sections of different solids are discussedd. An example of counting the number of cubes in a complex arrangement is discussed at the end.

column5: సౌష్ఠవం (Symmetry) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: In this video, the concept of symmetry is explained. Line and rotational symmetry are subsequently explained. Illustrative examples are given for better understanding.

column5: నిష్పత్తి మరియు దానిఅనువర్తనాల (Ratio and it's applications) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: The concepts and notations related to ratios are covered in this chapter. The unitary method and direct proportionality are explained using real life examples.

column5: భిన్నాలు మరియుఆకారణీయ సంఖ్యల ౧/౨(Fractions and Rational Numbers 1/2) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: This video explains the different concepts related to fractions like proper, improper, mixed fractions etc. Also, operations on fractions like multiplication, division etc. are explained.

column5: భిన్నాలు మరియుఆకారణీయ సంఖ్యల ౨/౨(Fractions and Rational Numbers 2/2) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: In this second part, learn about the addition of fractions having different denominators, reciprocal of fractions, rational numbers and the representation of rational numbers on the number line.

column5: త్రిభుజాల నిర్మాణం(Construction of Triangles) - Class 7 - Telugu Maths
column7: In this video, the construction of triangles with various sets of initial information is given, like 3 sides, two sides and included angle, right angled triangle with a side and hypotenuse and a triangle with a side and two angles. Illustrative examples are given for better understanding.
